[http://www.abocom.com.tw/product_download.aspx?name_id=D9FD1EA37934644AE6091A55FB5080FD Downloads] "M01-914M+-A10" is silkscreened on the board. This board is highly homologous to the [[HotBrick SoHo 401W]] / [[SerComm IP806SM]]. This may be indicative of usage of the same [http://investor.marvell.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=120802&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=481084&highlight= Marvell reference design] or evidence of SerComm involvement in the design (likely). :According to djb, [http://wikidevi.wi-cat.ru/files/archive/djnetbsd_old/Marvell%20Libertas%20Wireless%20Routers.htm the board was designed by SerComm]. The [http://www.abocom.com.tw/product_download.aspx?name_id=D9FD1EA37934644AE6091A55FB5080FD firmware for the ARM914] corroborates this as the firmware contains strings indicating SerComm authorship.
